{quote}When used in other supported stages, [{{$sum}}|https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/sum/#mongodb-group-grp.-sum] has one of two syntaxes:
 * [{{$sum}}|https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/sum/#mongodb-group-grp.-sum] has one specified expression as its operand:

{code:java}
{ $sum: <expression> } {code}
 

 * [{{$sum}}|https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/sum/#mongodb-group-grp.-sum] has a list of specified expressions as its operand:
{code:java}
{ $sum: [ <expression1>, <expression2> ... ]  } {code}
 {quote}
Only the 2nd syntax is implemented, because we thought it functionally covered the first with a single expression array.

But in the 1st syntax, the expression can resolve to an array.

Example : [https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/addFields/#using-two--addfields-stages]

See [https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/dateDiff/]
